changeSet.author: BilisS
changeSet.comment: Updates the MULTIPLE Classification value to the appropriate respective value
changeSet.sql:
update compliant_entity ce set allocation_classification = CASE WHEN get_remaining_quantity(ae1) > 0 and get_remaining_quantity(ae2) > 0 THEN 'UNDER_ALLOCATED' WHEN 0 > get_remaining_quantity(ae1) and 0 > get_remaining_quantity(ae2) THEN 'OVER_ALLOCATED' WHEN get_remaining_quantity(ae1) = 0 and get_remaining_quantity(ae2) = 0 THEN 'NOT_ALLOCATED' WHEN ((get_remaining_quantity(ae1) = 0 and get_remaining_quantity(ae2) > 0) or (get_remaining_quantity(ae1) > 0 and get_remaining_quantity(ae2) = 0)) THEN 'UNDER_ALLOCATED' WHEN ((get_remaining_quantity(ae1) = 0 and 0 > get_remaining_quantity(ae2)) or (0 > get_remaining_quantity(ae1) and get_remaining_quantity(ae2) = 0)) THEN 'OVER_ALLOCATED' WHEN get_remaining_quantity(ae1) > 0 and 0 > get_remaining_quantity(ae2) THEN CASE WHEN ABS(get_remaining_quantity(ae1)) > ABS(get_remaining_quantity(ae2)) THEN 'UNDER_ALLOCATED' WHEN ABS(get_remaining_quantity(ae2)) > ABS(get_remaining_quantity(ae1)) THEN 'OVER_ALLOCATED' WHEN ABS(get_remaining_quantity(ae1)) = ABS(get_remaining_quantity(ae2)) THEN 'COMPLIANT' END WHEN 0 > get_remaining_quantity(ae1) and get_remaining_quantity(ae2) > 0 THEN CASE WHEN ABS(get_remaining_quantity(ae1)) > ABS(get_remaining_quantity(ae2)) THEN 'OVER_ALLOCATED' WHEN ABS(get_remaining_quantity(ae2)) > ABS(get_remaining_quantity(ae1)) THEN 'UNDER_ALLOCATED' WHEN ABS(get_remaining_quantity(ae1)) = ABS(get_remaining_quantity(ae2)) THEN 'COMPLIANT' END END from allocation_entry ae1, allocation_entry ae2, allocation_year ay where ae1.compliant_entity_id = ce.id and ae1.allocation_year_id = ay.id and ae2.compliant_entity_id = ce.id and ae2.allocation_year_id = ay.id and (ae2.type != ae1.type) and ce.allocation_classification = 'MULTIPLE';
DROP FUNCTION IF EXISTS get_remaining_quantity(bigint, bigint, bigint, bigint);
